issue.title: Fission is synonymous to trouble!
issue.body:
Fission has a lot of issues which must be reflected to the community so that this project can be saved! 
First of all, there is actually no documentation (yes there's a very small and brief documentation which covers just the CLI). For example, where can we find documentation on how to create custom environments and custom builders? How is the function passed to the runtime? How is the function built if required? and so on.  (your official Go image was updated 2 years ago! Go 1.17 seriously?)

The other problem is that your repository is full of typos, errors, and outdated information. For example refer to your `examples` repo and you see that the README files are just copied and pasted without any revision. The Go example talks about Python! 

The `environment` repo is either providing invalid information or is outdated. I tried to build the env and builder images exactly by copying all docker commands and Fission failed to start the function! 

And now the big problem, when I said "Fission failed to start the function" that is the only information I could get `error executing HTTP request: Get "http://127.0.0.1:37019/fission-function/helloworld": context deadline exceeded`, how about some logs, traces, reasons? 

I am surprised that I heard about Fission from the CNCF community!! This project is not production ready yet!!

comment.body:
Hi @Vedadiyan,

If you can provider more info on Kubernetes version and Fission version you are using can help.
> One quick issue possible, please see if you have network policies enabled in the cluster and if its blocking cross namespace communication.

Fission environments are guideline images. TBH we haven't been updating them last couple of months. 
As you are aware go itself releases couple versions every year.
Current images we have are guideline images and most of users endup customizing them.

We do our best effort to try to answer queries, although we can agree things haven't been that consistent last couple of months.
I am trying to put my personal bw as much as possible and get things back on track. 

Fission tries to provide as much as control possible so most of users endup customizing Fission peripherals and using Fission core whenever the latest version is available.

I am closing this issue. Feel free to reopen if you need help debugging more on Fission.

+
+	t.Run("function", func(t *testing.T) {
+
+		envName := "test-func-env"
+		testFuncName := "hello"
+
+		_, filename, _, ok := runtime.Caller(0)
+		require.True(t, ok)
+
+		helloFuncFilePath := path.Join(path.Dir(filename), "hello.js")
+
+		_, err = cli.ExecCommand(f, ctx, "env", "create", "--name", envName, "--image", "fission/python-env")
+		require.NoError(t, err)
+
+		t.Run("create", func(t *testing.T) {
+			_, err := cli.ExecCommand(f, ctx, "function", "create", "--name", testFuncName, "--code", helloFuncFilePath, "--env", envName)
+			require.NoError(t, err)
+
+			testFunc, err := fissionClient.CoreV1().Functions(metav1.NamespaceDefault).Get(ctx, testFuncName, metav1.GetOptions{})
+			require.NoError(t, err)
+			require.NotNil(t, testFunc)
+			require.Equal(t, testFuncName, testFunc.Name)
+			require.Equal(t, envName, testFunc.Spec.Environment.Name)
+		})
